-- CADP (CONSTRUCTION AND ANALYSIS OF DISTRIBUTED PROCESSES)
-- http://cadp.inria.fr

This directory contains the following files:

 - cadp.el:         main entry point giving access to all CADP languages

 - bes-mode.el      Emacs/XEmacs mode for the BES format
 - exp-mode.el      Emacs/XEmacs mode for the EXP format
 - lnt-mode.el      Emacs/XEmacs mode for the LNT language
 - lotos-mode.el    Emacs/XEmacs mode for the LOTOS language
 - mcl-mode.el      Emacs/XEmacs mode for the MCL language
 - nupn-mode.el     Emacs/XEmacs mode for the NUPN format
 - rbc-mode.el      Emacs/XEmacs mode for the RBC format
 - svl-mode.el      Emacs/XEmacs mode for the SVL language
 - xtl-mode.el      Emacs/XEmacs mode for the XTL language

 - lotos-aux.el     additional features for lotos-mode.el
                    (developed by Mihaela Sighireanu)
 - lnt-aux.el       additional features for lnt-mode.el
                    (developed by Frederic Lang, Hugues Evrard, and Eric Leo)
 - svl-aux.el       additional features for svl-mode.el
                    (developed by Eric Leo)


These files were found to work properly for both GNU Emacs version 22.0.91.2
and XEmacs version 21.4.

(The "snippets" directory contains additional features; see its README file)

How to use these files:
-----------------------

In your home directory, create a ".emacs" file if it does not exist already.

Insert the following line in this file:

<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<

(load  (concat (getenv "CADP") "/ext/emacs/cadp.el"))

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>


